		{
			"type": "action",
			"name": "Spine Ripper",
			"system": {
				"actionType": {
					"value": "passive"
				},
				"description": {
					"value": "<p>Whenever a riispa slain a medium or smaller creature it also removes the creature's spine (if the creature has it). A creature who has the spine removed in this way cannot be resurrected until the spine is retrieved. A creature who has its spine removed in this way cannot be raised as a corporeal undead (e.g. a zombie or a skeleton), but can be raised as an incorporeal undead (e.g. a ghost, specter or similar)-.</p>",
